election_record.label: Connecticut 1804 Council of Assistants, Nomination

overview.note: The Connecticut Herald October 23, 1804 and Connecticut Gazette, and the Commercial Intelligencer October 31, 1804 both list the vote break down by County. Both list 12209 votes for Oliver Ellsworth, 12538 votes for Chauncey Goodrich, 12466 votes for Matthew Griswold and 7905 votes for Rufus Hitchcock, but the county totals add up to the above totals.
"Spencer, Hull and Warren lost votes for want of junior being added - It is probably therefore that E. Starr had the least support." Windham Herald (Windham, CT). November 1, 1804.

sub_unit.name: Fairfield
sub_unit.note: The New England Republican (Danbury, CT) lists William Hillhouse with 1650 votes, Jabez Clark with 1338 votes and Thomas Seymour with 1511 votes.

sub_unit.name: Danbury
sub_unit.note: "Votes for Assistants to stand in Nomination: FEDERAL. Highest 191. Lowest 182. Average votes 186. DEMOCRAT. Highest 156. Lowest 139. Average votes 148." Connecticut Herald (New Haven, CT). September 25, 1804.

sub_unit.name: Norwich
sub_unit.note: The Courier (Norwich, CT) lists Ebenezer Barnard as Ebenezer Barns.

sub_unit.name: Stonington
sub_unit.note: True Republican September 26, 1804 did not list the name of Ebenezer Devotion.
